    </div>

    <p>The mechanism is straightforward: creatine saturates muscle stores of phosphocreatine, which serves as the immediate energy source for high-intensity efforts lasting 0-10 seconds (heavy lifts, sprints, explosive movements). With more phosphocreatine available, you can maintain higher power output for additional reps — the extra training volume is what drives the additional muscle growth. Creatine does not build muscle directly; it enables you to train harder, which builds muscle indirectly through progressive overload.</p>

