    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How much creatine do I need daily?</summary>
      <p>The ISSN recommends 3-5g of creatine monohydrate daily. 5g fully saturates stores in 3-4 weeks. 3g is adequate for lighter individuals. A loading phase (20g/day for 5-7 days) accelerates saturation but is optional.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is creatine monohydrate or HCL better?</summary>
      <p>Creatine monohydrate is the gold standard with 500+ supporting studies. HCL is more water-soluble (less bloating) but has far less research. The ISSN recommends monohydrate specifically. Choose HCL only if monohydrate causes GI issues.</p>
    </details>

